Nodemon is a useful cli utility that watches the current directory and restarts its node process if any files change.

~~~ bash
$ npm i -g nodemon
~~~

**Watch specific directories**

~~~ bash
$ nodemon --watch ./src --watch ./lib <entrypoint>
~~~

**Ignore certain files**

~~~ bash
$ nodemon --ignore *.spec.js <entrypoint>
~~~

**Watch files with specific extentions**

~~~ bash
$ nodemon -e js,json,ejs,html,css,scss <entrypoint>
~~~

**Use babel-node**

~~~ bash
$ nodemon --exec babel-node <entrypoint>
~~~